FIG. 1 shows a structure of a conventional tap for compressed or liquefied gases which has an overcharging prevention function;


FIG. 2 shows a diagram for explaining an operation of a cam in a conventional tap;


FIG. 3 shows a whole configuration of a tap for compressed or liquefied gases which has an overcharging prevention function in accordance with an embodiment of the present invention;


FIG. 4 shows main parts in FIG. 3 under a low level of the charged gas;


FIG. 5 shows main parts in FIG. 3 during the charging of the gas; and


FIG. 6 shows main parts in FIG. 3 under a full-charging level of the gas.
